  "text": "In the sequel, we will consider two different code families: random codes and structured codes, namely polar codes [CITATION_1] . Both have codeword length N = 16 and code rate r = 0.5. While random codes are generated by randomly picking codewords from the codeword space with a Hamming distance larger than two, the generator matrix of polar codes of block size N = 2 n is given by",
